		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Mobile</placeName> <date>April 7 1851</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee>&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Respected Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Enclosed please<lb/> find &#36;20.00 it being nine Dollars subscription<lb/> of <persName>Israel H Jones</persName> &#38;c met.  4.00 <sic>arrearrs</sic> &#38; the subscription<lb/> for the ensuing year.  Please take notice of the same<lb/> in the Occident.  the Balance of 11.00 you will please give<lb/> me credit for the Thalith.  Other <add>&#63;</add> I have not yet<lb/> made.  <persName>Myer</persName> of <placeName>Montgomery</placeName> promises to send me 6.00 which<lb/> is all he owes bal.  <persName>Philip</persName> is at present absent.  You will do<lb/> me a favour by sending me a list of all your subscribers<lb/> &#38; their <sic>indebtness</sic>&#59; I have written to <persName>Mr. I Hart</persName> <placeName>N. O.</placeName><lb/> for a statement of Books I recvd<add>&#63;</add> from him&#59; &#38; if you will<lb/> let me know the amt you <add>&#63;</add> from me for Books<lb/> I shall forthwith send you the Blln if there is any<lb/> I have been so careless that I have not taken any notice<lb/> of the money I sent you.  The <add>Hebrew</add> I have not yet<lb/> disposed of&#44; but <persName>Mr Cohen</persName> told me last night that<lb/> he probably may take a <sic>sett</sic>.  You will send a copie<add>&#63;</add><lb/> of the Occident to J. <hi rend="underline"><persName>Loewenstein</persName> <placeName>Marion Miss</placeName></hi>.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><persName>Mr. L Lyons</persName> &#38; <persName>S. Levy</persName> of <placeName>Mobile</placeName> whose names as<lb/> subscribers I <sic>handet</sic> you when here&#44; have not recd<lb/> the Occident.  You may send me 1 doz copies of prayer<lb/> books <sic>german</sic> minhag &#38; 1 doz. spelling books.  Send the same to <persName>Mr. C. Nussbaum</persName> <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> as I expect<lb/> Books <add>&#63;</add> from him.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We are taken now action slips here of building<lb/> a synagogue.  A lot is already purchased&#59; building<lb/> will be <add>&#63;</add> forthwith.  The brickwork is to be<lb/> finished by next fall&#44; when the basement which is<lb/> to serve hereafter for a schoolroom is to be <sic>fittet</sic><lb/> up for a temporary place of worship&#44; to save any<lb/> farther rent.  The whole when finished will cost about<lb/> &#36;15.000.  After which the cong will no doubt engage a<lb/> efficient lecturer if any are to be found.  How would<lb/> <persName>Rev. I Leeser</persName> determine<add>&#63;</add> if he should be solicit to tell<lb/> the Israelites <del>their sins</del> of <placeName>Mobile</placeName> their sins&#63;<lb/> &#38; to lead them into they path of virtue &#38; religion.  <sic>if</sic><lb/> he would consent&#44; I am sure the congn would warmly<add>&#63;</add><lb/> &#38; with our accord accept him as their pastor.<lb/>  Consider the above not as a question to be answered<lb/> by you&#44; they are merely random thoughts&#44; but that<lb/> much I will say&#44; that much good can be done here among<lb/> the Israelites&#44; &#38; that a minister like the above named<lb/> &#38; may</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>effect much good &#38; I am sure they all would hail<lb/> such an event with the utmost delight &#38; pleasure I<lb/> rem more than your humble servant.&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am my dear sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours very truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">B H Emanuel</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><add>Hebrew</add></p>
		</body>
